have recommended most to other people?

1163
01:45:10,280 --> 01:45:18,840
I was given a book by my first coach, Nathan 
Seward seven years ago called The Big Leap  

1164
01:45:18,840 --> 01:45:28,200
by Gay Hendricks that I've recommended so many 
times. And it's based on this idea that we tend  

1165
01:45:28,200 --> 01:45:33,720
to self-sabotage ourselves when we experience 
too much success or too much happiness. And  

1166
01:45:33,720 --> 01:45:40,320
that that's linked to I think five things 
that would happen to us when we're growing  

1167
01:45:40,320 --> 01:45:46,680
up. One of them is the... What is it, the wild 
poppy syndrome or something like that. Like the  

1168
01:45:46,680 --> 01:45:51,080
tallest poppy is the one that's cut first. 
So if you shine in a family of siblings,  

1169
01:45:51,080 --> 01:45:53,800
then anytime you shine too much we're going 
to say, "Hey, hey, hey, that's not cool for  

1170
01:45:53,800 --> 01:46:00,920
the others." So that's going to be internalized 
and hardwired in your body and as an adult, as  

1171
01:46:00,920 --> 01:46:06,080
soon as you start shining a little bit too much, 
you're going to do the same thing to yourself. So  

1172
01:46:06,080 --> 01:46:14,320
the idea is going from having this point above 
which you can't be happy to turning it into,  

1173
01:46:14,320 --> 01:46:20,440
he calls it an upward-facing spiral with no upper 
limit. It's a really exciting and empowering book.

